params.amount: The amount to exercise expressed in units of currency.
The amount to mint expressed in units of currency.

swap(uint256,uint256,address).details: If some of the options are exercised, but the price of the asset goes back up, anyone can swap the assets for the original currency. The main reason for this is that minted gets locked once any option is exercised. When all assets are swapped back for currency, further minting can happen again.

params.assetAmount: The amount to swap. This is denominated in asset (NOT currency!) so it's always possible to swap ALL assets, and rounding won't leave dust behind.

withdraw(uint256,uint256,address).details: Withdraw from the pool. Asset and currency are withdrawn to the proportion in which they are exercised.

params.amount: The amount to withdraw expressed in units of the option.

withdrawEarly(uint256,uint256,address).details: Withdraw from the pool before expiry by returning the options. In this case Assets are withdrawn first if available. Only currency is returned if assets run to 0.

params.amount: The amount to withdraw expressed in units of the option.
